<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/4 (Thu.) How can we learn from what happened to others? / Your thought on Taiwan, Hong Kong and China (Host: Lawrence)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=396&amp;p=413#p413"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">*** Removal Notice ***<br />Thursday gathering of Royal Club is relocated to Ikari 怡客咖啡, 台北市衡陽路116號</span><br /><br />Session 1: How can we learn from what happened to others?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://focustaiwan.tw/culture/202005260016">https://focustaiwan.tw/culture/202005260016</a><!-- m --> 吳朋奉<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.damaxww.com/post1085857">http://www.damaxww.com/post1085857</a><!-- m --> 銀霞<br /><br />1.    Do you think there is a relationship between physical and mental health?<br />2.    Do you think Melancholia and Depression inborn or acquired先天或後天? (林青霞’s mother, 吳念真, suffering from depression) <br />3.    How can you get over life disaster, like loss of loved one? Divorced? Financial loss? Job?<br />4.    Do you think it’s safe for the elderly to live alone?<br />5.    We  can always learn from others’ life experience, good or bad (health, love relationship, success, -----.) Please share story or example ----.<br /><br />------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 2: Your thought on Taiwan, Hong Kong and Mainland China<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-52765838">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-52765838</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.    What do you think of Hong Kong security law just passed last week?<br />2.    Have you been to Hong Kong or Mainland china? What impressed you the most?<br />3.    What's your hope for Hong Kong and relationship between Taiwan and mainland China<br />4.    What do you think of Taiwan’s policy toward Mainland China?<br />5.    Would you like to work or do business or travel to Hong Kong or Mainland china? Why or why not?<br /><br />======================================================================<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 pm-7:30 pm Free talk<br />7:30 pm-8:10 pm Session 1 discussion<br />8:10 pm-8:40 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:40 pm-8:45 pm Break time &amp; Group picture<br />8:45 pm-9:15 pm Session 2 discussion<br />9:15 pm-9:30 pm Presentation<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25437">Michael</a> — Sat May 30, 2020 11:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
